          <div class="col-left"><a href="/en/news/most-outstanding-promoters-integration-year-were-announced"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.kul.ee/sites/kulminn/files/styles/news_list_thumbnail/public/news-cover-images/loimumispreemiate_saajad_2.jpg?itok=4Bq-SQT1" width="100" height="67" alt="Lõimumispreemiate saajad (autor: Viktor Burkivski)" title="Lõimumispreemiate saajad (autor: Viktor Burkivski)" /></a></div>
<div class="col-right">
  <div class="views-field-created">04.12.2020<span class="spacer">|</span>Ministry of Culture</div>
  <h2 class="views-field-title"><a href="/en/news/most-outstanding-promoters-integration-year-were-announced">The most outstanding promoters of integration of the year were announced</a></h2>
  <div class="views-field-body"><p>Today, Minister of Culture T&otilde;nis Lukas and Irene K&auml;osaar, Director of the Integration Foundation, announced the list of most outstanding promoters of integration for the year. Recognition and a financial prize were awarded to the non-profit Estonian Union of National Minorities, Estonian Refugee Council and Changemakers, as well as Arkadi Popov, the Director of the Emergency Medicine Centre of the North Estonia Medical Centre.</p></div>
</div>    </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even views-row-last">
      
          <div class="col-left"><a href="/en/news/saaremaa-was-enriched-two-more-cultural-monuments"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.kul.ee/sites/kulminn/files/styles/news_list_thumbnail/public/news-cover-images/1_sadama_lauter_vaade_merele_mailiroio.png?itok=dVjyTP-M" width="100" height="66" alt="Sadama rannalauter (foto: Maili Roio)" title="Sadama rannalauter (foto: Maili Roio)" /></a></div>
<div class="col-right">
  <div class="views-field-created">01.12.2020<span class="spacer">|</span>Ministry of Culture</div>
  <h2 class="views-field-title"><a href="/en/news/saaremaa-was-enriched-two-more-cultural-monuments"> Saaremaa was enriched by two more cultural monuments </a></h2>
  <div class="views-field-body"><p>Minister of Culture <strong>T&otilde;nis Lukas</strong> designated a century-old landing site for fishing boats, and the watermill on Simmu Farm in the village of M&ouml;ldri as cultural monuments. The landing site is still in use and the mill is unique because it has been rebuilt into a watermill.</p></div>
</div>    </div>
